  "content": "an>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    Every brainstorm, every decision, every rejected alternative gets persisted. When I revisit a topic, I see what I explored before and what changed since.\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-red); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">&#10060;</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 20px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-red); margin-bottom: 12px;\">Without Persistence</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 17px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8;\">\n        &#8226; Re-explore the same topic from scratch<br>\n        &#8226; Forget why an approach was rejected<br>\n        &#8226; Miss when the landscape changed<br>\n        &#8226; Knowledge evaporates between sessions\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">&#9989;</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 20px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-green); margin-bottom: 12px;\">With Persistent Memory</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 17px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8;\">\n        &#8226; See what was explored before<br>\n        &#8226; Understand why decisions were made<br>\n        &#8226; Track what changed since last visit<br>\n        &#8226; Knowledge compounds over time\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-purple); padding: 24px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-purple); margin-bottom: 12px;\">How It Works</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;\">\n      I use corvia (the project I'm building) to persist all research. Claude queries the knowledge base at the start of every session. Prior decisions, rejected alternatives, and design rationale are all searchable.\n    </div>\n  </div>",
